caption: Great local spot with a good HH (tasty food) and arcade games.

A relatively new spot on H St., Bar Elena strives to capture the eclectic, funky, effortlessly hipster vibe. The cartoonish modern art, arcade games and music selections are consistent with their desired audience, the elder millennials/ junior Gen Xers, and Alanis Morissette. Happy hour is fair priced @ $5-9 and gimmicks rotate based on day of the week (game night, half price items, mystery beer...) Food is okay, wings were spot on, burger is good, but it's compete with Sticky Rice, who does tots better... Little slow on service but still okay. Worth a tryout for friends and fam, a little too loud for a date.

After a long rideshare trip, my boyfriend and I caught the last ten minutes of happy hour at Bar Elena.  I enjoyed the Blake's Grizzly Pear Hard Cider, Our Fancy Nachoes, and 1/2 Dozen Oysters on the Half Shell.  The Blake's Grizzly Pear Hard Cider was sweet, light, fruity, dry, and smooth.  Their Fancy Nachos consisted of crispy corn tortillas loaded with pico, crema, cotija, radish, cilantro, lime, black bean puree, and braised brisket.  The 1/2 Dozen Oysters on the Half Shell was served with mignonette, cocktail sauce, and lemon. I liked how fresh they were.

not worth the time or the money. if you're just looking to grab a drink and made a bite or two at the bar, this place isn't a bad deal, but for a sit down dinner there are better options on H street.  service was sub par. waiter didn't know the menu, the bar options, what was available and what wasn't. never said he was new or just started, so we assumed he's just incompetent.  food over all was disappointing. party of four, ordered three apps, and we all got entrees. hush puppies, shrimp cocktail, and the chicken liver mousse to start. hush puppies were the only tasty item, shrimp cocktail with the shells still on makes the customer work for no reason, and the mousse lacked zero flavor or depth with these gigantic non-toasted toast points. so 1-3  For entrees i got the steak frites, mom the eggplant parm, boyfriend a burger, and friend the veggie nachos (vegan). My steak was cooked well, decent cut, but the frites were not fried or crispy and is half the meal so damn. Mom liked the eggplant parm, which was basically grilled eggplant with sauce on top.  boyfriends burger came on two pieces of toast, which wasn't on the menu or what he expected, so that was a bust also with limp undercooked fries. but the worst was the nachos where the waiter was dropping them off and handed an extremely hot plate to my friend that burned her hand. Now, she and i both cook and have worked in service before, so we know what happens when the kitchen leaves a plate under the hot lamps, but you don't hand that to a customer, you warn them and set the plate on the table for them.  A quick apology and he was gone, no manager stopped by to make sure she was ok, nothing. so after that we finished, paid and left and as a owner who lives off h street i don't plan on coming back nor suggesting this place to anyone.

Good service and delicious food. I tried the burger, oysters, hushpuppies and their tap beer. Everything was tasty. The cocktail shrimp was overcooked therefore extremely expensive. The atmosphere is good. They have arcades, pinball machines and other games. My wife and I liked the bar at first. We tried it a couple days after they opened and have been back a few times. However, it is very disappointing that in such a short period of time, they are doing the same as the majority of restaurants in the area which is to raise the price and decrease the amount of food or quality of the food so I have to downgrade them to a 3 star place. It is ok without being anything special just an average new restaurant that wants to recover their investment in one week with overpriced food and drinks.
The food and atmosphere are great here! The cocktails are fantastic and the bartenders gave me some great recommendations based on my personal tastes. A welcome addition to the area!

Cozy wood-and-brick plus art space with games and a jukebox playing "vintage" hip hop, alternative and international  (ie the music of our youth, if you too went to high school in the 90s). Tasty hand-ground burgers with that good bacon, oysters fresh and flavorful, poblano hushpuppies--sounds odd, tastes delicious.  The housemade hot and cocktail sauces were both addictive and sneaky spicy in good way. Friendly and efficient service even as the place filled up opening weekend.  We'll be back for more burgers and raw bar.  Hope to see a non-poutine clam chowder creep onto the seafood and modern comfort food focused menu.
